WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:03.769
Dre:<i> Lately,</i>
<i>there have been some changes</i>

00:03.771 --> 00:05.437
<i>around the Johnson household.</i>
Dre: Babe.

00:05.439 --> 00:06.672
[ Grunts ] Ah, hey, baby.

00:06.674 --> 00:07.973
Yeah, hey.

00:07.975 --> 00:09.675
I've been thinking, you know,
with you being pregnant,

00:09.677 --> 00:12.444
maybe you should take it easy,
focus on you and my baby.

00:12.446 --> 00:13.879
Why you keep saying "my," Dre?

00:13.881 --> 00:15.848
You know we haven't gotten
the swab back yet.

00:15.850 --> 00:17.950
You know I do not like it
when you make that joke

00:17.952 --> 00:20.452
because the subtext is
you're cheating on me.

00:20.454 --> 00:21.720
Subtext?
I...

00:21.722 --> 00:24.390
I was going to say maybe
you should take some time off

00:24.392 --> 00:26.058
because you worked so hard

00:26.060 --> 00:28.227
during all
of your other pregnancies.

00:28.229 --> 00:30.396
Well, that's really sweet,
but can we afford it?

00:30.398 --> 00:31.730
We'll figure it out.

00:31.732 --> 00:33.899
I'm pretty sure the layoffs
at work are behind us.

00:33.901 --> 00:35.234
Oh.

00:35.236 --> 00:38.070
Well, this brings me
great sadness to do this,

00:38.072 --> 00:41.640
especially since you grabbed me
this delicious Egg McMuffin

00:41.642 --> 00:44.843
on your drive into work,
but I really have no choice.

00:44.845 --> 00:47.813
Lucy...
we're laying you off.

00:47.815 --> 00:49.748
What? S-Seriously?

00:49.750 --> 00:51.917
Oh, my... oh, my God.

00:51.919 --> 00:53.752
Okay, that was a big lie.

00:53.754 --> 00:54.987
[ Laughs ] Whew!

00:54.989 --> 00:55.988
[ Laughs ]

00:55.990 --> 00:57.423
God, you got me going.

00:57.425 --> 00:58.757
Good one.

00:58.759 --> 01:00.926
It, uh, it didn't bring me
great sadness,

01:00.928 --> 01:02.428
but you<i> are</i> still laid off.

01:02.430 --> 01:03.429
That part was true.

01:03.431 --> 01:04.997
Dre: What the hell
is going on?

01:04.999 --> 01:07.066
I thought
the layoffs were over.
Stevens:
Oh, no, no, no.

01:07.068 --> 01:08.934
The tighter the ship,
the bigger the profits.

01:08.936 --> 01:12.004
Besides,
Daphne really hates Lucy.

01:12.006 --> 01:14.440
What?! We're getting our nails
done together at lunch.

01:14.442 --> 01:15.941
Well, that's gonna be awkward.

01:15.943 --> 01:19.411
Now, turning to Charlie.

01:19.413 --> 01:20.546
So, that's what's up?

01:20.548 --> 01:22.414
You brought me back here
so you can fire me?

01:22.416 --> 01:24.683
You think by telling me
in front of all these people,

01:24.685 --> 01:26.185
you think
I ain't gonna make a scene?

01:26.187 --> 01:29.088
All I got left
is my God and my goatee!

01:29.090 --> 01:31.256
Aaah!

01:31.258 --> 01:32.558
Hey, Charlie!

01:32.560 --> 01:34.760
[ Grunts ]

01:34.762 --> 01:35.527
No.

01:35.529 --> 01:36.628
Charlie.

01:36.630 --> 01:38.130
[ Grunts ]

01:38.132 --> 01:40.032
Calm down, Charlie!

01:40.034 --> 01:41.066
Aah!

01:41.068 --> 01:42.301
Oh, no, no, no.

01:42.303 --> 01:43.769
Ugh.

01:43.771 --> 01:44.937
Aaah!

01:44.939 --> 01:47.873
Charlie, you are not fired,
okay?!

01:47.875 --> 01:51.276
I was actually gonna say good
job on the Forever 21 campaign.

01:51.278 --> 01:54.646
Actually, that was me.

01:54.648 --> 01:55.647
Oh, that was a good job.

01:55.649 --> 01:57.049
I've seen it everywhere.

01:57.051 --> 01:59.151
On buses, schools.
It's all over the place.

01:59.153 --> 02:00.586
Really nice work there, Lucy.

02:00.588 --> 02:02.087
Okay.

02:02.089 --> 02:03.822
Well, now that
that is taken care of,

02:03.824 --> 02:06.625
it is time
for birthday announcements.

02:06.627 --> 02:09.962
Oh, well, looks like
we're not just celebrating

02:09.964 --> 02:11.263
Lucy's last day.

02:11.265 --> 02:14.433
♪ Happy bir... ♪
Come on.

02:14.435 --> 02:15.934
Come on, guys, help me out.

02:15.936 --> 02:19.404
♪ Happy ♪... scootchies...
♪ Happy birthday... ♪

02:19.406 --> 02:21.974
Jo-Josh,
I was just fired, okay?

02:21.976 --> 02:24.276
Oh. Um...

02:24.278 --> 02:26.645
I-I'm sorry.
I'll ju... I'll just...

02:26.647 --> 02:29.615
No, you don't have to...

02:29.617 --> 02:31.783
So slow.
Oh, for God...

02:31.785 --> 02:32.918
No, no, make a wish!

02:32.920 --> 02:34.186
Make a wish!
[ Cheering ]

02:34.188 --> 02:36.021
<i>And sometimes,</i>
<i>change isn't great...</i>

02:36.023 --> 02:37.022
That's yummy.

02:37.024 --> 02:38.190
<i>Especially if you're Lucy.</i>

02:38.192 --> 02:39.358
<i>It makes you wonder who's next.</i>

02:39.360 --> 02:40.459
Do you want a corner?

02:40.461 --> 02:41.460
No, no, no, <i>I</i> want the corner.

02:41.462 --> 02:42.742
Give her something
in the middle.

02:48.936 --> 02:51.103
Hey, baby, how was your day?

02:51.105 --> 02:52.871
Uh, not good.
I actually had to s...

02:52.873 --> 02:54.106
Good.

02:54.108 --> 02:56.108
Listen,
you're never going to believe

02:56.110 --> 02:58.177
what happened to me
at my doctor's appointment.

02:58.179 --> 03:02.481
Dr. Gonzales told me
that I have a geriatric womb.

03:02.483 --> 03:04.149
Uh, to your face?

03:04.151 --> 03:05.884
Told me that
I'm of advanced maternal age.

03:05.886 --> 03:07.486
To your face?!
Yes.

03:07.488 --> 03:08.887
Oh, baby, come here.

03:08.889 --> 03:09.888
It was awful.

03:09.890 --> 03:10.989
Relax, baby.

03:10.991 --> 03:12.291
Just means
your wife's uterus is old.

03:12.293 --> 03:13.292
What?

03:13.294 --> 03:14.293
Thank you, Ruby.

03:14.295 --> 03:16.128
Like "Antique Road Show" old.

03:16.130 --> 03:17.896
Like probably watches
"Murder, She Wrote"

03:17.898 --> 03:19.231
and has a landline<i> old!</i>

03:19.233 --> 03:21.233
Mama!
We get it.

03:21.235 --> 03:22.901
[ Laughs ]
Pops:
That's crazy.

03:22.903 --> 03:24.303
Look at her.

03:24.305 --> 03:26.972
She is a beautiful, vibrant,
curvy, vivacious young woman.

03:26.974 --> 03:28.640
Hey, hey,
pump your brakes, Pops.

03:28.642 --> 03:31.543
Not only is this my wife...

03:31.545 --> 03:33.178
but she is asleep.

03:33.180 --> 03:34.179
Bow!
[ Claps hands ]

03:34.181 --> 03:35.414
Huh?
Oh, my God.

03:35.416 --> 03:37.249
I'm so exhausted.

03:37.251 --> 03:39.418
Dre, m-maybe I should
take that time off.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.386
Really?

03:41.388 --> 03:42.821
Well...

03:42.823 --> 03:44.489
I think you taking some time off
is a good idea, sweetheart.

03:44.491 --> 03:46.391
And stand-up move
on your part, son,

03:46.393 --> 03:48.227
letting your wife
kick her feet up

03:48.229 --> 03:49.995
while you hold your family down
like a man.

03:49.997 --> 03:51.430
Mm-hmm. I agree.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.899
Her body obviously needs rest.

03:53.901 --> 03:54.900
Well...
Look at her.

03:54.902 --> 03:56.268
She's falling apart.

03:56.270 --> 03:57.903
Okay.
Listen here,
son.

03:57.905 --> 04:00.372
There's a good chance
I may have to carry this baby,

04:00.374 --> 04:01.673
and I'm willing to do it.

04:01.675 --> 04:05.110
The doctors say I have the
uterus of a 16-year-old Latina.

04:05.112 --> 04:06.411
[ Laughs ] Uh...

04:06.413 --> 04:08.180
Diane:
Mmm, smells good, Grandma.

04:08.182 --> 04:10.115
Mmm, what's on the menu?

04:10.117 --> 04:13.852
Well, it's Ruby Tuesday,
so you know what that means.

04:13.854 --> 04:15.887
Another
gravy-heavy experience.

04:15.889 --> 04:17.923
Dad, you need to make
the down payment

04:17.925 --> 04:19.558
for my summer trip abroad.

04:19.560 --> 04:21.927
And we need new bow and arrows
for "Hunger Games" camp.

04:21.929 --> 04:23.762
We're sending them
to "Hunger Games" camp?

04:23.764 --> 04:26.064
Isn't that ex...
violent?

04:26.066 --> 04:27.933
I don't know, and I don't care.

04:27.935 --> 04:30.602
All I know is they
take them away for two weeks

04:30.604 --> 04:31.737
and I don't see them.

04:31.739 --> 04:33.238
[ Chuckles ]

04:33.240 --> 04:35.307
That's a lucky baby
in that dusty womb of yours.

04:35.309 --> 04:38.076
Oh, and don't forget
my deposit for summer school.

04:38.078 --> 04:39.578
Didn't you get straight A's?

04:39.580 --> 04:43.081
Yeah, but this is
Advanced Summer Wizardry.

04:43.083 --> 04:46.418
My sorcery coach says I might
actually be a real wizard.

04:46.420 --> 04:47.986
Zoey: Really?

04:47.988 --> 04:49.988
<i>So, while everyone was excited</i>
<i>about their time off from work</i>

04:49.990 --> 04:52.624
<i>and expensive summer plans,</i>

04:52.626 --> 04:54.926
<i>I decided to drown my worries</i>

04:54.928 --> 04:57.963
<i>in some biscuits and gravy</i>
<i>and classic TV.</i>

04:57.965 --> 05:01.166
Announcer:<i> Get cozy</i>
<i>for an all-night marathon</i>

05:01.168 --> 05:03.335
<i>of your favorite</i>
<i>'70s Chicago sitcom.</i>

05:03.337 --> 05:04.436
<i>That's right.</i>
♪<i> Ain't we lucky we got 'em ♪</i>

05:04.438 --> 05:07.639
<i>Every episode back to back.</i>

05:07.641 --> 05:09.508
♪ Good times ♪

05:09.510 --> 05:11.243
Reporter:
<i>There's been an alarming rise</i>

05:11.245 --> 05:12.411
<i>in the unemployment rate</i>

05:12.413 --> 05:14.280
<i>in the black community</i>
<i>in Chicago,</i>

05:14.281 --> 05:16.148
<i>hitting highs of 19%.</i>
[<i> Audience cheers and applauds</i> ]

05:16.150 --> 05:18.950
That ain't news.
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

05:18.952 --> 05:21.953
[<i> Applause</i> ]

05:21.955 --> 05:23.922
Hey, Thelma.
Keith.

05:23.924 --> 05:25.324
Baby, I'm so glad you're home.

05:25.326 --> 05:26.491
I, uh...

05:26.493 --> 05:28.327
I got something to show you.

05:28.329 --> 05:29.494
Oh.

05:29.496 --> 05:31.630
What's this, baby?

05:31.632 --> 05:33.765
It's a pregnancy test.

05:33.767 --> 05:35.267
Man. [ Chuckles ]

05:35.269 --> 05:37.936
Technology has come a long way.

05:37.938 --> 05:39.104
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

05:39.106 --> 05:40.605
Keith...

05:40.607 --> 05:42.607
I'm pregnant.

05:42.609 --> 05:45.110
[<i> Audience gasps</i> ]

05:45.112 --> 05:47.112
Are you sure?

05:47.114 --> 05:48.947
Of course I'm sure.

05:48.949 --> 05:52.951
This thing is 26% accurate
65% of the time.

05:52.953 --> 05:54.286
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

05:54.288 --> 05:56.722
Keith, how did we
let this happen?

05:56.724 --> 06:00.225
Broke, living in the projects
at my parents' house.

06:00.227 --> 06:01.760
[ Sighs ]

06:03.831 --> 06:05.731
I'm just gonna be
another statistic.

06:05.733 --> 06:08.033
Hey, hey, hey, baby,
I-I know you're scared.

06:08.035 --> 06:09.368
Hell, I'm scared, too,

06:09.370 --> 06:12.637
and, no, you ain't gonna be
no nother statistic.

06:12.639 --> 06:15.574
Baby, I got my big
football tryouts coming up,

06:15.576 --> 06:18.844
and, hey, when I do go pro,
we're gonna get married.

06:18.846 --> 06:21.246
And... And I'm gonna have enough
money to take care of everybody

06:21.248 --> 06:22.581
<i>and</i> buy a fancy car!

06:22.583 --> 06:24.916
Baby, I'm gonna be
an NFL football player,

06:24.918 --> 06:26.685
and they don't ever go broke!

06:26.687 --> 06:28.186
Huh?!
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

06:28.188 --> 06:29.187
Oh, baby.

06:29.189 --> 06:31.490
Oh, you make me feel
so much better.

06:31.492 --> 06:32.491
Oh.
Oh.

06:32.493 --> 06:33.925
And who knows?
Hmm?

06:33.927 --> 06:35.394
Maybe Daddy <i>won't</i> be mad.

06:35.396 --> 06:36.361
[ Junior scoffs ]

06:36.363 --> 06:38.397
That don't sound right.

06:38.399 --> 06:39.664
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

06:39.666 --> 06:40.999
J.J.?

06:41.001 --> 06:42.868
[<i> Cheers and applause</i> ]

06:42.870 --> 06:43.935
Uh, 'tis I.

06:43.937 --> 06:45.103
[<i> Applause</i> ]

06:45.105 --> 06:47.205
Didn't we tell you
about eavesdropping?

06:47.207 --> 06:49.174
You told me,
but I think it's safe to say

06:49.176 --> 06:50.842
I didn't give a damn.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.177
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

06:52.179 --> 06:53.845
Until we decide how we're gonna
tell Daddy the news,

06:53.847 --> 06:55.447
you keep
your big ol' mouth shut.

06:55.449 --> 06:58.216
As long as you let me be there
when you tell him.

06:58.218 --> 07:00.752
I ain't never painted
a murder scene before.

07:00.754 --> 07:02.754
[<i> Cheers and applause</i> ]

07:02.756 --> 07:06.925
Damn! You ain't gonna believe
what happened to me today.

07:06.927 --> 07:08.393
You got your paycheck
cut in half?

07:08.395 --> 07:09.928
They doubled your workload?

07:09.930 --> 07:11.530
The cops hassled you
on the way home?

07:11.532 --> 07:13.465
No, I found
a really good parking spot

07:13.467 --> 07:14.900
in front of the building.

07:14.902 --> 07:19.271
Man, you people have
an incredibly fatalistic
outlook on life.

07:19.273 --> 07:22.240
Hey, Mrs. Evans.
Hey, Michael.

07:22.242 --> 07:24.309
Hey, what's going on?

07:24.311 --> 07:27.412
I just left
the principal's office.

07:27.414 --> 07:30.649
Apparently,
your son staged a walk-out

07:30.651 --> 07:31.983
for the school lunch monitors.

07:31.985 --> 07:33.452
They got us down there
busing tables

07:33.454 --> 07:34.753
and washing trays for cheap.

07:34.755 --> 07:36.421
Then tell them what happened.

07:36.423 --> 07:38.757
Julio and his cousin Julio

07:38.759 --> 07:41.760
said that they'd do our job
for half the pay.

07:41.762 --> 07:43.128
What?!

07:43.130 --> 07:46.064
If he thinks that Mexicans
are gonna come do the dirty work

07:46.066 --> 07:47.933
that black folks do
for less money,

07:47.935 --> 07:49.601
he's got another thing coming.

07:49.603 --> 07:51.436
Mm-hmm.
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

07:51.438 --> 07:52.671
Hey, hey.

07:52.673 --> 07:53.939
You keep fighting for the people
like you are, man,

07:53.941 --> 07:55.907
you might just become
our first black president.

07:55.909 --> 07:57.843
Yeah, but not in these
United States of America.

07:57.845 --> 07:58.944
Oh, unh-unh.

07:58.946 --> 08:00.245
No, 'cause that ain't never
gonna happen.

08:00.247 --> 08:01.480
Not ever, ever.

08:01.482 --> 08:03.248
Ever, ever, ever, ever!

08:03.250 --> 08:04.249
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

08:04.251 --> 08:05.517
Ruby:
Now he's got no job.

08:05.519 --> 08:07.018
I had to leave mine early

08:07.020 --> 08:09.254
and walk 30 blocks
to get him from school.

08:09.256 --> 08:10.922
Got attacked by a dog.

08:10.924 --> 08:14.626
Would've lost my big toe had
the sugar not already taken it.

08:14.628 --> 08:16.027
Mm!
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

08:16.029 --> 08:17.095
Oh, well.

08:17.097 --> 08:19.164
Tomorrow's gonna be
a better day.

08:19.166 --> 08:23.101
Tomorrow might be a better day,
but not nine months from now.

08:23.103 --> 08:24.669
Hey.
Be cool, fool.

08:24.671 --> 08:26.037
I<i> am</i> cool.

08:26.039 --> 08:28.874
She's the one in heat.

08:28.876 --> 08:31.042
Oh, thank goodness for you,
baby girl.

08:31.044 --> 08:32.377
Once you finish college,

08:32.379 --> 08:35.146
you're gonna make everything
right for this family.

08:35.148 --> 08:37.315
I disagree.

08:37.317 --> 08:38.517
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

08:38.519 --> 08:39.684
Sorry.

08:39.686 --> 08:42.187
I don't know why I said that.

08:42.189 --> 08:44.823
Even though she's my daughter,

08:44.825 --> 08:48.159
I feel much more of a kinship
with Keith.

08:48.161 --> 08:50.495
Oh.
Thank you, Mrs. Evans.

08:50.497 --> 08:52.631
No, baby, call me Mama.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.065
Well, Mama, I...

08:54.067 --> 08:55.467
Unh-unh.
Oh.

08:55.469 --> 08:57.335
You call me Mrs. Evans.

08:57.337 --> 08:58.470
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

08:58.472 --> 08:59.571
Uh-oh.

08:59.573 --> 09:03.074
Almost forgot my evening
turtleneck in the dryer.

09:03.076 --> 09:07.245
I got me a hot blind date
with a fine young tender.

09:07.247 --> 09:11.416
I think it's safe to assume that
all your dates are blind, J.J.

09:11.418 --> 09:13.084
[<i> Cheers and applause</i> ]
-Hey.
-Hey.

09:13.086 --> 09:15.086
Hey, Wilona.
Hey, Penny.

09:15.088 --> 09:17.255
Hey, J.J.
Sorry we're late.

09:17.257 --> 09:19.591
Everybody's late around here.

09:19.593 --> 09:21.526
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

09:21.528 --> 09:23.395
How can you be late?
You weren't invited.

09:23.397 --> 09:24.829
Nice to see you, too, friend.

09:24.831 --> 09:27.899
Julio told me that
Julio and Julio stole your job.

09:27.901 --> 09:29.501
Penny, be nice.

09:29.503 --> 09:30.902
That<i> was</i> me being nice.

09:30.904 --> 09:31.903
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

09:31.905 --> 09:34.205
Are we here in time for gravy?

09:34.207 --> 09:36.708
Can't, Penny.
Fresh out of gravy.

09:36.710 --> 09:38.176
Just add more water, Mama.

09:38.178 --> 09:39.611
Can't.

09:40.514 --> 09:42.113
Fresh out of water.
What?

09:42.115 --> 09:43.882
I thought Bookman fixed it.

09:43.884 --> 09:45.050
[ Grunts ]

09:45.052 --> 09:47.218
[<i> Cheers and applause</i> ]

09:47.220 --> 09:48.620
Almost fixed.

09:48.622 --> 09:52.691
12 to 14 hours,
and we'll be halfway there.

09:52.693 --> 09:56.461
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

09:57.864 --> 10:00.031
Boy, what the hell happened
to your shirt?

10:00.033 --> 10:02.767
Apparently,
Bookman fixed the dryer.

10:02.769 --> 10:05.604
So, you want wet water
and a less dry dryer?

10:05.606 --> 10:07.639
You people are so demanding.

10:07.641 --> 10:08.907
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

10:08.909 --> 10:10.809
Pregnancy test?

10:10.811 --> 10:12.143
[<i> Audience "Oohs"</i> ]

10:12.145 --> 10:14.913
You have to take a test
to get pregnant?

10:14.915 --> 10:18.984
No, it's a test to see
if you<i> are</i> pregnant.

10:18.986 --> 10:22.320
Really?
This tiny little thing?

10:22.322 --> 10:24.656
[<i> Laughter</i> ]
Well,
whose is it?

10:24.658 --> 10:26.424
Well, don't look at me.

10:26.426 --> 10:28.093
[ Scoffs ] Don't look at me.

10:28.095 --> 10:29.094
Don't look at me.

10:29.096 --> 10:30.962
Ain't nobody
looking at you, woman!

10:30.964 --> 10:32.030
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

10:39.906 --> 10:44.275
Mama... Daddy...[sighs]

10:44.277 --> 10:45.410
I'm pregnant.

10:45.412 --> 10:47.746
Oh, Thelma!

10:47.748 --> 10:50.248
I'm gonna need more red paint.

10:50.250 --> 10:52.817
White Jesus, white Jesus!

10:52.819 --> 10:55.186
Why have thou forsaken me?

10:55.188 --> 10:56.621
How did this happen?

10:56.623 --> 10:59.491
More importantly,
<i>where</i> did this happen?

10:59.493 --> 11:02.193
Because there is clearly
only one bed in here

11:02.195 --> 11:03.662
that we all sleep in.

11:03.664 --> 11:07.098
Okay, everything
is going to be fine.

11:07.100 --> 11:08.800
Boy, do you have
the slightest idea

11:08.802 --> 11:10.335
what it means to have a child?

11:10.337 --> 11:12.671
Did you even consider the cost?

11:12.673 --> 11:16.474
The diapers, the formula,
the medical bi... shots.

11:16.476 --> 11:17.942
We'll skip the shots.

11:17.944 --> 11:19.511
We skipped the shots
with J.J.!

11:20.514 --> 11:22.013
We'll need the shots.
We need the shots.

11:22.015 --> 11:25.183
We already got 82 people
living in this house.

11:25.185 --> 11:28.153
We don't need an 83rd,
no matter how small.

11:28.155 --> 11:31.823
And with our luck,
it'll have Thelma's appetite...

11:31.825 --> 11:33.058
and face.

11:33.060 --> 11:35.694
Hey, J.J, can I rap to you
outside for a second?

11:35.696 --> 11:37.228
Oh, sure.
Oh, all right.

11:37.230 --> 11:38.730
Hey, man, I was thinking.

11:38.732 --> 11:41.266
Once Thelma gives birth
to this baby...

11:43.170 --> 11:45.670
All right, look, everybody,
I will be able

11:45.672 --> 11:49.074
to take care of Thelma
and the baby forever.

11:49.076 --> 11:53.344
The NFL takes care of its
players<i> long</i> after they retire.

11:53.346 --> 11:56.848
♪♪

11:56.850 --> 11:58.483
Hey, Florida.

11:58.485 --> 12:00.251
James, it's midnight.

12:00.253 --> 12:02.353
You're home from work early.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.756
Aw, they wouldn't let me work
a quadruple shift.

12:04.758 --> 12:05.890
[ Smooches ]

12:05.892 --> 12:07.726
Say, what's with
all the empty photo albums?

12:07.728 --> 12:09.594
Oh, I was just
sitting here imagining

12:09.596 --> 12:12.063
what our old wedding photos
would've looked like

12:12.065 --> 12:13.832
if we could've afforded
a camera.

12:13.834 --> 12:15.033
[ Laughs ]

12:15.035 --> 12:16.534
Look at you, James.

12:16.536 --> 12:18.169
Look here.
Look at me.

12:18.171 --> 12:19.871
You remember
how nervous you were

12:19.873 --> 12:22.006
when we found out
we were expecting a child?

12:22.008 --> 12:23.108
Ooh!
[ Both laugh ]

12:23.110 --> 12:24.242
Just like Keith,

12:24.244 --> 12:26.945
you had all the hopes and dreams
in the world.

12:26.947 --> 12:28.580
I was never like Keith.

12:28.582 --> 12:31.349
No, I had hopes and dreams
and four jobs.

12:31.351 --> 12:32.350
[ Chuckles ]

12:32.352 --> 12:34.686
Hopes and dreams
don't feed a family.

12:34.688 --> 12:38.189
Nobody ever asked for a second
helping of hopes and dreams.

12:39.192 --> 12:41.092
James, where you going?

12:41.094 --> 12:43.762
Well, where do you think
I'm going, Florida?

12:43.764 --> 12:46.131
I'm going to work.

12:46.133 --> 12:48.633
[ Telephone rings ]

12:48.635 --> 12:49.768
Hello?

12:49.770 --> 12:52.370
J.J.,
some lady for you.

12:52.372 --> 12:56.608
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

12:57.744 --> 12:59.811
[ Clears throat ]

12:59.813 --> 13:01.412
Uh, chello?

13:01.414 --> 13:03.715
[<i> Laughter</i> ] Oh, hey, baby.

13:03.717 --> 13:05.150
Keith, how did it go?
How were tryouts?

13:05.152 --> 13:06.384
Dre: Should've seen me,
Thelma.

13:06.386 --> 13:07.619
I took the snap,

13:07.621 --> 13:09.754
and I ran a sweep to the left
and scampered a few yards,

13:09.756 --> 13:12.090
I came up short, then boom,
I turned it to the right,

13:12.092 --> 13:13.324
I took it to the house!

13:13.326 --> 13:14.659
[ Chuckles ]

13:15.962 --> 13:18.963
It went really well, guys.

13:18.965 --> 13:20.965
See, James? I told you
Keith was gonna be able

13:20.967 --> 13:22.433
to take care
of our little girl.

13:22.435 --> 13:23.968
Yeah, well,
we'll see about that.

13:23.970 --> 13:27.238
I knew everything
was gonna be all right.

13:27.240 --> 13:30.341
Keith is gonna be
the next O.J. Simpson.

13:30.343 --> 13:31.409
God willing.

13:31.411 --> 13:33.411
Oh, yeah.
God willing.

13:33.413 --> 13:34.579
[ Laughter ]

13:34.581 --> 13:36.414
I'll finish dinner.

13:36.416 --> 13:39.484
Afterwards, we're gonna try
this thing I heard about

13:39.486 --> 13:40.852
called dessert.

13:40.854 --> 13:42.153
What's that?

13:42.155 --> 13:46.958
Well, it's a little meal
white folks have after dinner.

13:46.960 --> 13:48.459
Like breakfast?

13:48.461 --> 13:50.929
Yeah,
but... but sweet.

13:50.931 --> 13:52.463
Sweet breakfast?

13:52.465 --> 13:54.499
Yeah, but at night.

13:54.501 --> 13:55.700
Ah.
Mm-hmm.

13:55.702 --> 13:58.002
Sweet night breakfast.
Mm-hmm.

13:58.004 --> 14:00.004
Like sugar eggs.

14:00.006 --> 14:03.074
Yeah.
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

14:07.280 --> 14:10.048
[<i> Audience gasps</i> ]

14:10.050 --> 14:11.850
[ Groans ]

14:11.852 --> 14:14.953
That don't look good.

14:14.955 --> 14:16.521
♪♪

14:22.629 --> 14:24.395
Surprise! Surprise!
Surprise! Surprise!

14:24.397 --> 14:26.331
Florida:
It's the man of the hour!

14:26.333 --> 14:28.132
What are we celebrating?

14:28.134 --> 14:30.168
You, babe, and your success.

14:30.170 --> 14:33.071
Now, we know
this is mystery meat, baby,

14:33.073 --> 14:35.573
but when you make it
to the pros,

14:35.575 --> 14:39.010
you're gonna be eating
the finer things of life,

14:39.012 --> 14:41.379
[Chuckles] like imitation crab.

14:41.381 --> 14:43.648
[ Chuckles ]
Bookman:
Or fresh fruit.

14:43.650 --> 14:46.484
One of these days,
I'm gonna have me a strawberry.

14:46.486 --> 14:49.554
Hey, you guys,
I've got some good news myself.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.856
I am not gonna finish college.

14:51.858 --> 14:53.258
Florida:
What, Thelma?

14:53.260 --> 14:54.259
No, come on.

14:54.261 --> 14:55.693
I don't even think
I need a degree,

14:55.695 --> 14:58.229
with you getting drafted
by the Houston Oilers.

14:58.231 --> 15:01.032
I mean, that franchise
is gonna be around forever.

15:01.034 --> 15:02.166
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

15:02.168 --> 15:03.201
[ Door closes ]

15:03.203 --> 15:04.402
Hey, Dad, where you been?

15:04.404 --> 15:05.570
Work.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.839
Well, maybe when Keith makes it
to the NFL,

15:07.841 --> 15:10.074
you can get rid
of one of those jobs, James.

15:10.076 --> 15:12.043
[ Chuckles ]
Me with only
three jobs?

15:12.045 --> 15:14.913
I wouldn't even know what to do
with all that extra time.

15:14.915 --> 15:16.080
[ Chuckles ]

15:16.082 --> 15:17.882
Well... Well, how about
you take a day off?

15:17.884 --> 15:20.518
You know, I never imagined
myself with one of those.

15:20.520 --> 15:22.253
That seems like
the kind of thing

15:22.255 --> 15:24.255
that only white folks get,
like socks.

15:24.257 --> 15:25.690
With all that free time,

15:25.692 --> 15:27.759
you could possibly even
take up a hobby.

15:27.761 --> 15:28.860
Mm-hmm.

15:28.862 --> 15:30.361
Always did want to try
a REM sleep.

15:30.363 --> 15:32.263
Now that you've made it big,

15:32.265 --> 15:34.265
can you get me a hat
that covers my ears,

15:34.267 --> 15:36.301
'cause, you know,
this city's really windy.

15:36.303 --> 15:37.402
[ Laughs ]

15:37.404 --> 15:38.803
And can I get
some art supplies?

15:38.805 --> 15:40.138
Canvasses, paintbrushes.

15:40.140 --> 15:42.607
Will you buy me glasses
with a prescription?

15:42.609 --> 15:45.376
I've always wanted to see
what you guys look like.

15:45.378 --> 15:46.911
All right, enough!

15:46.913 --> 15:48.313
Uh, Penny, no.

15:48.315 --> 15:51.215
You're just gonna have to
recognize us by our voices.

15:51.217 --> 15:53.084
Look, I'm not going to the NFL.

15:53.086 --> 15:54.218
[ All gasping ] Aw.

15:54.220 --> 15:55.987
I hurt my knee
at football tryouts.

15:55.989 --> 15:57.722
Th-They tell me
I'll never play again.

15:57.724 --> 15:59.090
M-My football career
is over.

15:59.092 --> 16:00.858
I told you this guy was a bum!

16:00.860 --> 16:02.060
Daddy.

16:02.062 --> 16:03.494
No, no, no, Thelma,
your daddy's right.

16:03.496 --> 16:05.463
Look,
I-I-I-I don't deserve this.

16:05.465 --> 16:07.598
W-What kind of meat
is that, anyway?

16:07.600 --> 16:08.666
It doesn't matter.

16:08.668 --> 16:11.836
You don't deserve it...
none of it!

16:11.838 --> 16:13.338
Oh, James.

16:13.340 --> 16:15.573
Damn! Damn! Damn!

16:15.575 --> 16:17.408
[ Door slams ]

16:17.410 --> 16:20.812
[<i> Audience "Awws"</i> ]

16:20.814 --> 16:22.280
Why you got to be
so hard on him?

16:22.282 --> 16:23.581
Because he's a bum.

16:23.583 --> 16:27.652
I thought I was clear when
I said, "Keith, you're a bum!"

16:27.654 --> 16:29.087
You know what?

16:29.089 --> 16:32.824
You remember this handsome
young man on his wedding day?

16:32.826 --> 16:37.628
You know, when his dreams
didn't pan out, he made it work.

16:37.630 --> 16:39.263
I haven't had a dream
in 30 years.

16:39.265 --> 16:40.665
How could I?
I haven't slept!

16:40.667 --> 16:41.933
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

16:41.935 --> 16:45.303
I don't want our kids to
struggle like we did, Florida.

16:45.305 --> 16:47.105
Damn it.

16:47.107 --> 16:49.874
I want our kids
to have better than we did.

16:49.876 --> 16:53.444
I want them to have an album
filled with actual pictures.

16:53.446 --> 16:55.313
I want that, too.

16:55.315 --> 16:56.681
But until then,

16:56.683 --> 17:00.218
we got to have faith that Keith
will work it out like you did.

17:00.220 --> 17:01.386
[ Sighs ]

17:01.388 --> 17:04.088
What those kids need right now
is our support.

17:06.493 --> 17:08.726
Y'all, I'm sorry
I'm such a failure.

17:08.728 --> 17:11.963
I only had one dream my whole
life, and now it's over.

17:11.965 --> 17:14.298
A-And because of me,
this family's gonna remain

17:14.300 --> 17:17.235
poor, black,
and strawberry-less.

17:17.237 --> 17:18.403
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

17:18.405 --> 17:19.904
Listen, son, I understand
what you're going through.

17:19.906 --> 17:21.406
It's a struggle
to raise a family.

17:21.408 --> 17:25.576
But the good news is,
you don't have to do it alone.

17:25.578 --> 17:26.911
Florida:
That's right.

17:26.913 --> 17:27.912
Really?

17:27.914 --> 17:29.414
Yeah, we're here to help you.

17:29.416 --> 17:31.716
J.J.: Listen, man, I was gonna
take one of my sweet thangs out

17:31.718 --> 17:37.722
for a fine-dining extravaganza,
but you can have those $3.

17:37.724 --> 17:39.690
[<i> Laughter</i> ]

17:39.692 --> 17:41.759
And I can give you
this month's foster-care money

17:41.761 --> 17:43.027
for Penny and her sister.

17:43.029 --> 17:44.028
Uh...

17:44.030 --> 17:45.696
Uh, Penny doesn't have
a sister.

17:45.698 --> 17:48.166
Do you want the money or not?

17:48.168 --> 17:52.203
Hey, hey, y'all, thank you,
but I'll get by.

17:52.205 --> 17:53.538
Look, I'm just sorry

17:53.540 --> 17:55.540
I couldn't help you fulfill
your dream of sleeping.

17:56.376 --> 17:57.375
Or seeing.

17:57.377 --> 17:59.343
It's okay.
I can still hear.

17:59.345 --> 18:01.579
James: Yeah,
don't worry about it.

18:01.581 --> 18:04.248
Being poor, black, and tired
is all we've ever known.

18:04.250 --> 18:05.750
Hmm.

18:05.752 --> 18:07.218
Oh. Oh.
Oh. Oh.

18:07.220 --> 18:08.252
Oh, wow.

18:08.254 --> 18:09.754
Did you forget
to pay the power bill?

18:09.756 --> 18:11.556
Forgetting's for rich folks.

18:11.558 --> 18:12.590
We're just broke.

18:12.592 --> 18:14.725
Ah.

18:14.727 --> 18:17.428
Well, tomorrow's gonna be
a better day.

18:17.430 --> 18:19.263
Mm.
J.J.: Dy-no-mite.

18:19.265 --> 18:21.632
♪ Good ti-i-i-i-mes ♪

18:21.634 --> 18:24.702
♪ Yeah ♪

18:25.638 --> 18:28.940
<i>Good evening.</i>
<i>I'm James Earl Jones.</i>

18:28.942 --> 18:31.109
<i>Welcome to "Black Omnibus."</i>

18:31.111 --> 18:35.613
<i>Tonight, we discuss the height</i>
<i>of the Latin jazz movement</i>

18:35.615 --> 18:40.084
<i>with famed percussionist</i>
<i>Willie Bobo.</i>

18:40.086 --> 18:42.220
Well, well, well, well, well.

18:42.222 --> 18:43.421
Look who's alive.

18:43.423 --> 18:45.423
[<i> Chuckles</i> ] [ TV beeps ]

18:45.425 --> 18:47.725
That gravy nap
really set me back.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.093
Nap?

18:49.095 --> 18:51.429
Dre, seriously, you've been
asleep for like 12 hours.

18:51.431 --> 18:53.598
Oh, my...
Look at you.

18:53.600 --> 18:55.800
Oh, my God.
I was?

18:55.802 --> 18:57.335
Man, I must really be stressed

18:57.337 --> 18:59.470
about the baby and that
new round of layoffs at work.

18:59.472 --> 19:00.638
Another round?

19:00.640 --> 19:02.640
Sweetie, I thought
you said that was over.

19:02.642 --> 19:05.643
Ugh, I thought they were,
but it doesn't matter.

19:05.645 --> 19:08.112
Hey, hey, hey, it's okay...

19:08.114 --> 19:09.113
[ Sighs ]

19:09.115 --> 19:12.116
because I just had
a great dream.

19:12.118 --> 19:15.753
It made me realize
that it doesn't matter

19:15.755 --> 19:18.823
if we have less money
or more kids

19:18.825 --> 19:21.292
as long as we are together.

19:21.294 --> 19:22.527
[ Chuckles ]
Diane: Dad?

19:22.529 --> 19:23.528
Yep?

19:23.530 --> 19:25.263
If you're really worried
about money,

19:25.265 --> 19:26.797
I don't have to go
on that trip.

19:26.799 --> 19:29.033
Yeah,
and if I'm really a wizard,

19:29.035 --> 19:31.836
we'll never have to worry
about money again.

19:31.838 --> 19:33.037
[ Chuckles ]

19:33.039 --> 19:34.305
Or dragons.

19:34.307 --> 19:35.940
Oh.
There he is.

19:35.942 --> 19:38.109
You're welcome
to some of my allowance.

19:38.111 --> 19:40.311
I mean, it's not much,
but that's on you.

19:40.313 --> 19:42.079
Ah, touché.
[ Chuckles ]

19:47.453 --> 19:48.686
Don't look at me.

19:48.688 --> 19:50.988
I'm still learning
how to share.

19:50.990 --> 19:52.023
You know what?
Me, too.

19:56.229 --> 19:57.228
Aww. Ah, babe, look at us.
Look at that.

19:57.230 --> 19:58.062
That was the beginning.

19:58.064 --> 19:59.497
Aren't we cute?

19:59.499 --> 20:00.798
[ Chuckles ]

20:00.800 --> 20:01.799
Whoa.

20:01.801 --> 20:03.367
What's wrong with your eyes?

20:03.369 --> 20:04.869
Are you a demon?

20:04.871 --> 20:06.404
Rainbow: No, no, no, no, no.
It's called red eye.

20:06.406 --> 20:08.072
We didn't have anything
to fix it then.

20:08.074 --> 20:09.674
Also, she's a demon.

20:09.676 --> 20:10.675
Uh.

20:10.677 --> 20:12.043
Aww, look at that.

20:12.045 --> 20:13.177
Look, you're so cute.

20:13.179 --> 20:14.979
Diane: Ugh.
That was my awkward phase.

20:14.981 --> 20:16.814
Burn it.
[ Ruby laughs ]

20:16.816 --> 20:18.216
Hey, look at this one.

20:18.218 --> 20:20.318
It's a picture of Junior
in his awkward phase.

20:20.320 --> 20:22.186
I was a baby.

20:22.188 --> 20:23.221
Pops: Hey, y'all want to see
an awkward baby?

20:23.223 --> 20:25.089
Yes, please.
Mm-hmm.

20:25.091 --> 20:26.824
Look at this here.
This is Dre.
No way.

20:26.826 --> 20:28.426
Ohhh! Ohhh!
Ohhh! Ohhh!

20:28.428 --> 20:30.494
Look at that head. Doctor told
us he was gonna grow into it.

20:30.496 --> 20:32.263
We're still waiting, son.

20:32.265 --> 20:33.598
Same size.
[ Laughing ]
Same size.

20:33.600 --> 20:35.266
Looks like a watermelon.

20:35.268 --> 20:36.901
Diane: So big.
[ Laughter ]

20:36.903 --> 20:39.003
So you carry my picture around,
huh?

20:40.006 --> 20:42.006
It came with the wallet.

20:42.008 --> 20:44.175
Okay.

20:44.177 --> 20:45.243
Come on.
Turn the page, boy.

20:45.245 --> 20:46.877
Earl.

20:46.879 --> 20:48.346
I don't know.
[ Laughter ]

20:48.348 --> 20:50.248
I don't even remember,
where is this?

20:50.250 --> 20:51.415
Where did this happen?

20:51.417 --> 20:52.683
Yeah, where's this at?
